{"name": "pastel", "metadata": {"name": "pastel", "version": "0.2.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/sdispater/pastel", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Bring colors to your terminal.", "upload_time": 1600284071}, "documentation": ["# Pastel: Bring colors to your terminal\n\nPastel is a simple library to help you colorize strings in your terminal.\n\nIt comes bundled with predefined styles:\n\n- `info`: green\n- `comment`: yellow\n- `question`: black on cyan\n- `error`: white on red\n\n```{image} https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sdispater/pastel/master/assets/screenshot.png\n```\n\n## Features\n\n- Use predefined styles or add you own.\n- Disable colors all together by calling `with_colors(False)`.\n- Automatically disables colors if the output is not a TTY.\n- Used in [cleo](https://github.com/sdispater/cleo).\n- Supports Python **2.7+**, **3.5+** and **PyPy**.\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\n>>> import pastel\n>>> print(pastel.colorize('<info>Information</info>'))\n'Information'  # Green string by default\n>>> print(pastel.colorize('<fg=red;options=bold>This is bold red</>'))\n'This is bold red'\n```\n\n## Installation\n\n```\npip install pastel\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pastel", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [{"name": "pastel.colorize", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "message", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Formats a message to a colorful string.\n\n:param message: The message to format.\n:type message: str\n\n:rtype: str"]}, {"name": "pastel.with_colors", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "colorized", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Enable or disable colors.\n\n:param decorated: Whether to active colors or not.\n:type decorated: bool\n\n:rtype: None"]}, {"name": "pastel.add_style", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fg", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "bg", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "options", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Adds a new style.\n\n:param name: The name of the style\n:type name: str\n\n:param fg: The foreground color\n:type fg: str or None\n\n:param bg: The background color\n:type bg: str or None\n\n:param options: The style options\n:type options: list or str or None"]}, {"name": "pastel.remove_style", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Removes a style.\n\n:param name: The name of the style to remove.\n:type name: str\n\n:rtype: None"]}, {"name": "pastel.pastel", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "colorized", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns a new Pastel instance.\n\n:rtype: Pastel"]}], "variables": [{"name": "pastel.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pastel._PASTEL", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "pastel.Pastel", "xref": {"fqname": "pastel.pastel.Pastel", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "pastel.stack", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pastel.stack.StyleStack", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "pastel.stack.StyleStack.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "empty_style", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pastel.stack.